&lt;p&gt;&#160;The expression &quot;substr(t0.s, t1.i-1)&quot; has a nested function. The second parameter of substr is actually&#160;GenericUDFOPMinus. The ColStatistics on it doesn&apos;t have a valid range. But getRangeWidth doesn&apos;t check it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; Optional&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Double&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; getRangeWidth(Range range) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (range.minValue != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; range.maxValue != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Optional.of(range.maxValue.doubleValue() - range.minValue.doubleValue());
&#160; &#160; &#160; }
&#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Optional.empty();
&#160; &#160; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only 4 UDF classes implement StatEstimatorProvider and only UDFSubstr has this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17293681" author="robbie" created="Tue, 2 Mar 2021 13:01:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug can be worked around by setting&#160;hive.stats.estimators.enable to false.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
